      <data key="entity_id">IoU Threshold</data>
      <data key="entity_type">concept</data>
      <data key="description">IoU Threshold is a parameter in NMS that determines when two bounding boxes are considered overlapping based on their intersection over union.&lt;SEP&gt;IoU threshold is a parameter used in object detection to determine the overlap between bounding boxes.&lt;SEP&gt;IoU threshold is a parameter used in object detection to determine the overlap between predicted and ground-truth bounding boxes.</data>
