    <node id="RT-DETR Performance Comparison Chart (image)">
      <data key="entity_id">RT-DETR Performance Comparison Chart (image)</data>
      <data key="entity_type">image</data>
      <data key="description">This image presents Figure 1 from the paper 'DETRs Beat YOLOs on Real-time Object Detection'. It is a scatter plot comparing the proposed RT-DETR model against state-of-the-art YOLO variants (v5, v6, v7, v8) and PP-YOLOE. The chart demonstrates that RT-DETR achieves a better trade-off between accuracy (COCO AP) and inference speed (Latency on T4 GPU), effectively outperforming existing real-time detectors by eliminating the need for Non-Maximum Suppression (NMS).</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-d809e0e1bcdd4c9f8a94aed63c30ee41</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773520089</data>
    </node>
    <node id="RT-DETR Paper Page 2 - Related Work and Methodology (image)">
      <data key="entity_id">RT-DETR Paper Page 2 - Related Work and Methodology (image)</data>
      <data key="entity_type">image</data>
      <data key="description">This image shows page 2 of the RT-DETR research paper, detailing the methodology for the proposed Real-Time DEtection TRansformer. It outlines the efficient hybrid encoder and uncertainty-minimal query selection designed to overcome DETR computational bottlenecks. The page includes Figure 2, a bar chart showing box count vs. confidence thresholds, and Table 1, quantifying the impact of NMS hyperparameters on speed and accuracy. It also contains the 'Related Work' section reviewing YOLO and DETR architectures.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-e238e07664cabcd0111d4240219d3a67</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773520089</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Page 3 of Research Paper on Detector Speed and NMS Analysis (image)">
      <data key="entity_id">Page 3 of Research Paper on Detector Speed and NMS Analysis (image)</data>
      <data key="entity_type">image</data>
      <data key="description">This image is page 3 of a technical paper analyzing the end-to-end speed of object detectors. It features a bar chart comparing the number of output boxes for YOLOv5 and YOLOv8 at different confidence thresholds, and a table detailing the impact of IoU and confidence thresholds on Average Precision (AP) and Non-Maximum Suppression (NMS) execution time. The accompanying text explains the analysis of NMS hyperparameters and establishes a benchmark for comparing detector speeds.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-d827c15f5e7f24992576a42cc0d70b86</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773520089</data>
    </node>
    <node id="RT-DETR Performance Comparison Chart (image) [image_asset p0]">
      <data key="entity_type">image_asset</data>
      <data key="description">This image presents Figure 1 from the paper 'DETRs Beat YOLOs on Real-time Object Detection'. It is a scatter plot comparing the proposed RT-DETR model against state-of-the-art YOLO variants (v5, v6, v7, v8) and PP-YOLOE. The chart demonstrates that RT-DETR achieves a better trade-off between accuracy (COCO AP) and inference speed (Latency on T4 GPU), effectively outperforming existing real-time detectors by eliminating the need for Non-Maximum Suppression (NMS).</data>
      <data key="source_id">image_asset:img-99e7ffd2d8bdeacb7f3dbf73d0a79fa0</data>
      <data key="is_image_node">1</data>
